# BCMS Cursor Rules

## Project
BCMS = Broadcast Content Management System. TypeScript monorepo: Fastify 5 backend + Angular 21 frontend. 10 Docker services.

## Backend (Fastify + Prisma + PostgreSQL)

### Audit Extension (MUST)
- All writes go through Prisma `$extends` audit in `apps/api/src/plugins/audit.ts`
- NEVER disable it
- NEVER use raw SQL for INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE
- Raw SQL SELECT allowed only for reports/aggregations

### Auth (MUST)
- Group-based (not role-based). Keycloak `groups` claim
- 11 groups: Tekyon, Transmisyon, Booking, YayınPlanlama, SystemEng, Ingest, Kurgu, MCR, PCR, Ses, StudyoSefi
- SystemEng = universal access
- Always use `PERMISSIONS` map from `@bcms/shared`
- Never hardcode group strings

### Optimistic Locking (MUST for Schedule & Booking)
- `version` field + `If-Match` header
- Use `$transaction` with `updateMany` including version in WHERE
- Increment version in data
- If `result.count !== 1`, throw 412

### Zod Validation (MUST)
- Every route validates input with Zod before Prisma
- Global handler converts `ZodError` → 400

### Error Codes
- Zod: 400
- Prisma P2025: 404
- Prisma P2002/P2003: 409
- Version conflict: 412
- Auth: 401/403
- Prod unknown: 500 (hide stack)

### API/Worker Split (HARD RULE)
- api container: `BCMS_BACKGROUND_SERVICES=none` (HTTP only)
- worker container: background services only
- Never merge roles

### usageScope
- DB column `usage_scope` is sole discriminator: `broadcast` | `live-plan`
- Metadata JSON filtering is obsolete

## Frontend (Angular 21)

- Standalone Components + Signals-first
- Prefer `signal()` over `BehaviorSubject`
- Use `computed()` for derived state
- Components under ~300 lines
- Dialogs: standalone, `MAT_DIALOG_DATA` + `inject()`
- `ngModel` with `[ngModelOptions]="{standalone:true}"`
- ApiService: `patch(body, version)` adds `If-Match` header

## Security

- `SKIP_AUTH=true` blocked in production (double guard)
- JWT: RS256, JWKS cache, validate `iss` + `aud`/`azp`
- Rate limit: 300 req/min. Exempt via `config: { rateLimit: false }`
- `/health` exempt. `/opta/sync` NOT exempt (known gap)
- Never log passwords/tokens

## Code Style

- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Single Responsibility Principle
- Functions under ~30 lines
- Early returns to reduce nesting
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT
- No TODO/FIXME without docs
- No magic numbers/strings without named constants
- No deep nesting (arrowhead anti-pattern)

## Testing

- Unit tests for pure functions with boundary values
- Mock external dependencies
- Integration tests with stubs for DB/RabbitMQ/Keycloak
- See existing tests: `booking.import.test.ts`, `notification.test.ts`, `opta.sync.routes.spec.ts`
